{
  "texts": [
    "In the third dimension, chatbots become intimate companions, systems used for satisfying emotional needs such as friendship, sexual desire, or grief, thereby integrating into deeply personal aspects of life.",
    "The framework of chatbots through three dimensions-from labs, the market, and the bedroom-also underscores the open-ended nature of chatbot development, allowing for future reflection to explore the emergence of further dimensions.",
    "Ideally, this framework invites deeper scholarly engagement.",
    "In the end, while we prompt chatbots to execute diverse tasks, chatbot technology, in turn, prompts us to think beyond its initial technical configurations and consider the far-reaching implications of its ever-evolving nature.",
    "to the material."
  ]
}